        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>We at KINDERBRAIN are dedicated to protecting the privacy and rights of individuals in line with the Singapore Personal Data Protection Act 2012 (PDPA).</p>
    
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, process, and manage your personal data as part of our operations, including through our websites, digital services, and products such as mobile applications and other online or offline services. This Privacy Policy applies to any personal data in our possession or control.</p>
    
        <p>By interacting with us and providing your data, you consent to KinderBrain and our authorised service providers processing your personal data as described in this Privacy Policy. If you have any questions about this policy, please contact us using the details provided at the end of this document.</p>
    
        <p>This Privacy Policy adds to, but does not override, any previous consents you may have given us, and it does not affect our legal rights regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal data. We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or for compliance with legal requirements. When we make changes, the updated policy will be available on our website. Your continued use of our website and services constitutes your acceptance of the latest version of this Privacy Policy.</p>
    
        <p>This Privacy Policy was last updated on 11/8/2024.</p>
    
        <p>Please note that KinderBrain is responsible for operating our website and related services, including any updates, upgrades, and new versions.</p>
    
        <h2>1. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
    
        <p>1.1. "Personal Data" refers to any information that can identify an individual, either on its own or when combined with other information that we may have access to.</p>
    
        <p>1.2. Personal Data does not include business contact information, data contained in records that are over 100 years old, information about deceased individuals who have been dead for more than 10 years, or data that has been anonymized.</p>
    
        <p>1.3. The types of Personal Data we collect vary depending on your interactions with us. Examples of the Personal Data you may provide include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>(a) Personal details (e.g., name, identification numbers, contact information, residential address, personal email address, nationality, medical history, and income levels);</li>
            <li>(b) Images and biometrics (e.g., photographs, voice and video recordings, and biometric data such as fingerprint and facial recognition);</li>
            <li>(c) Your opinions or feedback shared with us (e.g., through surveys or direct communication); and</li>
            <li>(d) Electronic data related to your use of our services (e.g., location data, IP address, activity logs, device information).</li>
        </ul>
    
        <p>1.4. References to "Personal Data" also include information you provide about others, as described in section 3 below.</p>
    
        <p>1.5. Terms such as "includes," "including," and similar phrases are intended to be non-exhaustive and should be understood as "including without limitation."</p>
    
        <p>1.6. "Processing" of Personal Data includes any actions such as collection, recording, storage, alteration, retrieval, transmission, or deletion.</p>
    
